THIS CAN BE ARCHIVED BY "FORKING" THE ORIGINAL REPOSITORY.
YOU MAY NOT DISTRIBUTE THE ORIGINAL UNMODIFIED PROGRAM AT ALL.

THE CREATOR OF THE MODIFIED VERSION IS RESPONSIBLE FOR EVERY PROBLEMS AND LAW INFRIDGEMENTS HIS MODIFIED VERSION CAUSES. The original creator, BlackCetha, IS NOT RESPONSIBLE IN ANY WAY FOR MODIFIED VERSIONS.

This means specifically, but not limited to, that you may not make modified versions available to download on any third party site (exept github). You may still link to the GitHub repository.

If you're modifying the program, you need to state exactly what you modified. I would suggest editing the "readme.md" on GitHub.
If you find a bug or otherwise make a useful modification, feel free to create a pull request.

Hosting providers may ask for permission to distribute copies (unmodified or modified) of the program to their customers.

